Package BTO_Management_System

package BTO_Management_System
  • Class
    Description
    Applicant
    Represents an applicant in the BTO management system.
    Application
    Represents an application submitted by an applicant for a specific BTO project.
    ApplicationStatus
    Enumerates the possible statuses of a BTO application.
    BTOManagementApp
    The main application class for the BTO (Build-To-Order) Management System.
    BTOProject
    Represents a BTO (Build-To-Order) project managed by HDB.
    Date
    Represents a calendar date with day, month, and year components.
    Enquiry
    Represents an enquiry submitted by an applicant regarding a specific BTO project.
    FlatType
    Enumerates the different types of flats available in BTO projects.
    HDBManager
    Represents an HDB Manager, a type of user with administrative privileges to manage BTO projects, officer applications, applications from the public, withdrawal requests, project assignments, and generate reports.
    HDBOfficer
    Represents an HDB Officer, who can register to handle BTO projects, manage enquiries for their assigned project, and book flats for successful applicants.
    Interfaces
    This class serves as a container for all the interfaces defined within the BTO Management System.
    MaritalStatus
    Enumeration representing the possible marital statuses of an applicant.
    ProjectRegistry
    A registry class that holds and manages all BTO projects in the system.
    RegisterStatus
    Enumeration representing the possible statuses of a registration application submitted by an HDB Officer to handle a BTO project.
    RegistrationApplication
    Represents an application submitted by an HDBOfficer to register for handling a specific BTOProject.
    User
    Abstract base class for all users in the BTO management system.
    User.UserSettings
    Inner class to encapsulate user-specific settings related to project display, such as preferred locations, flat types, and sorting order.
